  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study is to see if using aromatherapy (Lavender or Bergamot) will lower
      anxiety in patients having invasive Radiology procedures. First, the level of anxiety is
      assessed prior to the procedure using a questionnaire. Then, patients are given the
      aromatherapy treatment during the pre-procedure period. Then, the same questions are asked to
      determine how anxious the patient is after the aromatherapy and before going into the
      procedure room. After the procedure, patients are asked to evaluate the process of the study.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
